data.name: cb_controls.ToolTip
data.value:
none: Use this setting if you set the assistance level via the Kingmeter display or if you only use the thumb throttle.
poti: Use this setting if you have a poti to set the assistance level.
soft-poti: Use this setting to emulate the poti with the thumb throttle. When the throttle switch is pressed once, the poti value will be set by the current throttle value.
up-down-switches: Will use two switches connected to the poti- and throttle switch-wires to control the assistance level.

data.name: cb_controlmode.ToolTip
data.value:
power: motor power is held constant at the value set by poti.
wh/km: the consumption is held constant at the value set by poti.
torque: motor power is proportional to driver power, factor is set by poti.

data.name: nud_controlmode.ToolTip

power mode: poti sets power between 0 and this value in watts
wh/km mode: poti sets consumption between 0 and this value in wh/km
torque mode: poti sets motor power between 0% and this value in % of the human power

data.name: chb_resetintegral.ToolTip
data.value:
If this is unchecked, the integral part of the PID regulator will slowly ramp down when you start braking. Thus the motor will restart at almost the same power, if you release the brake after a short time.
If this is checked, the integral part of the PID regulator will be set to zero if you are braking. Thus, it will take a bit more time for the motor to deliver its power after you release the brake, since the regulator has to start all over again. This is more safe but may be less comfortable.
The same behaviour is valid for the PAS sensor, too.
